        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2474485340" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7573965394867042701">What&apos;s in <b>your</b> garage?  Vehicles, auxiliary fridge, access to the furnace?  Seems normal enough, at least that&apos;s what is in my garage.  But let&apos;s say your garage has been converted into a workshop with access limited to an outside door.  And what if that outside entrance is kept locked?  Just what could your spouse be tinkering around with in there?  Hmmm?<br/><br/>Stillhouse Lake in Tennessee.  Sounds tranquil enough, but Gwen Proctor&apos;s carefully manufactured life is about to implode. She, along with her</span>
  <span id="freeText7573965394867042701" style="display:none">What's in <b>your</b> garage?  Vehicles, auxiliary fridge, access to the furnace?  Seems normal enough, at least that's what is in my garage.  But let's say your garage has been converted into a workshop with access limited to an outside door.  And what if that outside entrance is kept locked?  Just what could your spouse be tinkering around with in there?  Hmmm?<br /><br />Stillhouse Lake in Tennessee.  Sounds tranquil enough, but Gwen Proctor's carefully manufactured life is about to implode. She, along with her two kids, have worked hard to blend in and return to some semblance of normalcy.  This fourth identity change and move seemed to have been successful.    <br /><br />This was a real page turner for me.  Believable dialogue, nicely developed characters, and a plot that kept my interest throughout.  Enough to where I immediately requested the second book from our library.  Can't wait to break it open!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7573965394867042701" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
